<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="predict-vt">predict <strong><em>vt</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /prɪ'dɪkt/    美 /prɪ'dɪkt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-forecast">1.★ <strong>预言；预计 (forecast)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>predict tomorrow’s weather
预告明天的天气</p></div>

<ul>
<li>predict + (that) / wh- 从句：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Population experts predict that most people will live in cities in the near future. 
人口专家预言，在不久的将来大多数人都会住到城市里。</p><footer>2008 上海春</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It’s hard to predict when driverless cars will be everywhere on our roads.
很难预料何时我们的公路上才会出现大量的无人驾驶汽车。</p><footer>2018 北京</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>it is predicted + that 从句：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It was predicted that inflation would continue to fall.
据预测，通货膨胀率将继续下降。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>predictable /prɪ'dɪktəbl/ adj <br />
prediction /prɪ'dɪkʃn/ n [C] &amp; [U]   </p>
<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>No matter how carefully you plan your finances, no one can <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (预测) when the unexpected will happen.   （2014 浙江改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. predict / forecast  </p></div>